metadata.name: Anarchitecture Tokyo, Tower Records v1B
metadata.description:
WYSI*not*WYG project
(What You See Is *NOT* What You Get)

Anarchitecture Tokyo

This animated photograph is from the series Anarchitecture Tokyo made with digital photography. 

The original photographic series was presented at the Digaital Shoc festival held at Atsuko Barouh Gallery from February 28 to March 29, 2015 in Tokyo, Japan
Curated by Samson Sylvain

Specs:
1080*2048, 25 fps

Anarchitecture is an ongoing photographic series from the WYSI*not*WYG project.
Using fragmented images of a city photograph from around the world, the process remakes our urban landscape through digitally processed photos that break down and offer a new version of the reality of our day-to-day urban environment.
